cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a new architecture for learning spatio-temporal motion models from data alone, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a novel auto-encoder (cs.AI) and proposes new evaluation protocols (cs.RO) to assess the quality of synthetic motion sequences. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on motion-capture datasets (cs.GR).
